<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1658,1954]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
The trophi (
<figureCitation box="[340,428,1658,1684]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="17.[151,255,933,957]" captionTargetBox="[476,1110,181,933]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[476,1111,177,999]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 16. Testudinella patina, scanning electron microscope photographs of complete set of trophi. A. Frontal view. B. Caudal view. Scale bar: 10" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187532/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[396,428,1658,1684]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation box="[492,681,1658,1684]" pageId="16" pageNumber="19" refString="De Smet, W. H. (2005) Study of the trophi of Testudinella Bory de St. Vincent and Pompholyx Gosse (Rotifera: Testudinellidae) by scanning electron microscopy. Hydrobiologia, 546, 203 - 211." type="journal article">
De Smet (
<number box="[612,674,1658,1684]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
have 
<number box="[754,826,1658,1684]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="14.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="12.0">12–16</number>
/ 
<number box="[836,909,1658,1684]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="14.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="12.0">12–16</number>
(left/right) unci teeth, with very slender and only weakly offset heads; heads of major teeth fairly small. The manubria consist of three large superimposed chambers; sub-ventral chamber vestigial. The number of arched rami scleropili is ~ 
<number box="[1141,1214,1735,1761]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="31.5" valueMax="32.0" valueMin="31.0">31–32</number>
/ 
<number box="[1224,1297,1735,1761]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="30.5" valueMax="31.0" valueMin="30.0">30–31</number>
(left/right). The fulcrum lacks a proximal opening frontally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1658,1954]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Measurements. Lorica length 
<number box="[548,646,1812,1838]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="235.0" valueMax="350.0" valueMin="120.0">120-350</number>
µm, lorica width 
<number box="[855,953,1812,1838]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="168.0" valueMax="236.0" valueMin="100.0">100-236</number>
µ, distal foot pseudosegment 
<number box="[1305,1378,1812,1838]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="17.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="15.0">15–20</number>
µm. 
<taxonomicName box="[198,427,1851,1876]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Testudinellidae" genus="Testudinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Flosculariaceae" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="patina">
<emphasis box="[198,427,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Testudinella patina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an euryhaline cosmopolitan species, common in freshwaters rich in submerged vegetation, but also regularly reported from the marine littoral, and brackish and inland saline waters (
<bibRefCitation author="De" pageId="16" pageNumber="19" refString="De Ridder, M. &amp; Segers, H. (1997) Monogonont Rotifera recorded in the world literature (except Africa) from 1960 to 1992. Studiedocumenten van het K. B. I. N., 88, 481 pp." type="book" year="1997">
De Ridder &amp; Segers 
<number box="[353,415,1928,1954]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fontaneto" box="[427,681,1928,1954]" pageId="16" pageNumber="19" refString="Fontaneto, D., De Smet, W. H. &amp; Ricci, C. (2006) Rotifers in saltwater environments, re-evaluation of an inconspicuous taxon. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 86, 623 - 656." type="journal article" year="2006">
Fontaneto 
<emphasis box="[552,611,1929,1954]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[618,681,1928,1954]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
